---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import StakeCTA from '../components/StakeCTA.astro';

const schema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'FAQPage',
  mainEntity: [
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'What is Crazy Time game show?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Crazy Time is a live casino game show by Evolution Gaming. A real host spins a large 54-segment wheel in a purpose-built studio. Players bet on outcomes before each spin. Four bonus rounds — Coin Flip, Cash Hunt, Pachinko, and Crazy Time — can deliver multiplied payouts up to ×20,000.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Who makes the Crazy Time game show?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Crazy Time is developed and operated by Evolution Gaming (Evolution AB), a Swedish company listed on Nasdaq Stockholm. Evolution is the largest live casino supplier in the world and provides Crazy Time tables to hundreds of online casinos globally.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'When was Crazy Time released?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Crazy Time was released by Evolution Gaming in 2020. It quickly became one of the most watched and most bet-on live casino games worldwide.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Is Crazy Time a game show or a slot machine?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Crazy Time is a live casino game show, not a slot machine. It features a real physical wheel, live human hosts, and real-time interaction. Results come from a spinning wheel, not a software RNG like slots.' },
    },
  ],
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Crazy Time Game Show — How It Works, Who Makes It & Full Guide"
  description="Crazy Time explained as a game show: who makes it, how the format works, the four bonus games, and why it became the world's most popular live casino game."
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">
    <h1>Crazy Time Game Show: The Complete Guide</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-slate-300">
      Crazy Time is not a traditional slot machine or card game. It's a live casino game show — broadcast from a purpose-built studio, hosted by a real person, and watched by tens of thousands of players simultaneously. This guide explains exactly what makes Crazy Time a game show, who produces it, how the format is structured, and what separates it from every other casino game.
    </p>

    <h2>What Kind of Game Is Crazy Time?</h2>
    <p>
      Crazy Time sits in a category called "live game shows" — a genre that Evolution Gaming essentially invented and dominates. It combines a physical money wheel (similar to the TV show format of Wheel of Fortune or Deal or No Deal) with four interactive bonus round mini-games, all broadcast live via multiple camera angles with professional hosts and production-quality lighting and sets.
    </p>
    <p>
      The experience is closer to watching a television game show than playing at a traditional casino table. There's a studio audience atmosphere, enthusiastic hosts who interact with players through the chat interface, and real-time results that create genuine tension with every spin.
    </p>
    <p>
      Unlike software-based slots, there is no algorithm generating results on a server. A physical, certified wheel spins. A flapper lands on a segment. The outcome is real, visible, and verifiable — watched simultaneously by players around the world.
    </p>

    <h2>Who Makes Crazy Time?</h2>
    <p>
      Crazy Time is created and operated exclusively by <strong>Evolution Gaming</strong> (officially Evolution AB), a Swedish B2B live casino company founded in 2006 and listed on Nasdaq Stockholm. Evolution is the largest live casino supplier in the world by revenue and market share.
    </p>
    <p>
      Evolution does not sell directly to players. Instead, they provide the Crazy Time game as a licensed product to online casinos. When you play Crazy Time on Stake, Bet365, or any other platform, the game itself — the studio, the wheel, the hosts, the technology — is all Evolution's. The casino is just the distribution point.
    </p>
    <p>
      This matters for trust: Evolution holds gaming licenses from the Malta Gaming Authority, the UK Gambling Commission, and multiple other regulators. Their games are independently audited by agencies like eCOGRA and GLI. No individual casino can manipulate Crazy Time results because they don't control the game.
    </p>

    <h2>The Crazy Time Studio Setup</h2>
    <p>
      Crazy Time is filmed in Evolution's dedicated Crazy Time studio — an immersive, multi-level set designed specifically for the game. Key elements:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>The main wheel</strong>: A large, 54-segment physical wheel mounted vertically, lit with vibrant LED lighting. A flapper at the top determines the winning segment.</li>
      <li><strong>The top slot</strong>: A digital slot display above the wheel that spins before each round, randomly assigning a multiplier to one segment.</li>
      <li><strong>Three bonus doors</strong>: Separate rooms visible in the studio for the Pachinko board, Cash Hunt screen, and Crazy Time bonus wheel. Each activates when the corresponding segment wins.</li>
      <li><strong>Multiple cameras</strong>: High-definition cameras cover the wheel, the top slot, the host, and the bonus rooms from various angles, all cut by a live production team.</li>
      <li><strong>The host</strong>: A professional live presenter runs each round, announces results, interacts with the chat, and hosts bonus rounds with genuine energy.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>The Four Bonus Game Shows Within Crazy Time</h2>
    <p>
      What makes Crazy Time unique among wheel games is the four bonus rounds — each a mini game show in its own right:
    </p>

    <h3>1. Coin Flip</h3>
    <p>
      A large physical coin with different multipliers on each face is launched into the air. Players watch live as it spins and lands. The top slot can double the winning multiplier before the flip. Simple, fast, and surprisingly tense. Pays up to ×1,000 in rare cases.
    </p>

    <h3>2. Cash Hunt</h3>
    <p>
      A grid of 108 symbols fills the screen. All players simultaneously choose one symbol before a countdown ends. Then the symbols scatter randomly across the grid, each revealing a hidden multiplier. Players win whatever is behind their chosen symbol. Strategy has zero effect on outcome — but the suspense of watching symbols move is part of the show format. Learn more on the <a href="/cash-hunt-strategy">Cash Hunt strategy page</a>.
    </p>

    <h3>3. Pachinko</h3>
    <p>
      A physical pegboard with a puck dropped from the top. The puck bounces through pegs and lands in one of several multiplier slots at the bottom. Some slots show DOUBLE — if the puck lands there, all multipliers double and the puck drops again. This can cascade multiple times, theoretically reaching ×10,000. The physical nature of the puck dropping makes it visually compelling. Full breakdown at the <a href="/pachinko-strategy">Pachinko strategy page</a>.
    </p>

    <h3>4. Crazy Time (The Bonus Within the Bonus)</h3>
    <p>
      The most anticipated result. A giant second wheel — much larger than the main wheel — fills the screen. It has more segments and much higher multipliers than the main wheel. Players choose one of three flappers before the bonus wheel spins. If DOUBLE or TRIPLE segments appear on the wheel, all multipliers multiply accordingly before the final spin resolves. Maximum theoretical payout: ×20,000 on the bonus stake.
    </p>

    <h2>Why Crazy Time Became the World's Most Popular Live Game</h2>
    <p>
      Several factors combined to make Crazy Time the dominant live casino game show since its 2020 release:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Accessibility</strong>: Bets from $0.10 mean almost any player can participate. There are no complex rules to learn — you pick a segment and watch.</li>
      <li><strong>Spectacle</strong>: The production value is closer to a TV show than any casino game that existed before. The studio, lighting, and host energy create genuine entertainment even when you're not winning.</li>
      <li><strong>Community</strong>: Thousands of players watch the same wheel spin simultaneously. Chat interactions, shared reactions to near-misses, and collective excitement during bonus rounds create a social dimension slots cannot replicate.</li>
      <li><strong>Variance</strong>: The possibility of ×20,000 payouts — while mathematically rare — creates genuine excitement. Players regularly share Crazy Time bonus screenshots showing life-changing wins from small stakes.</li>
      <li><strong>Transparency</strong>: The physical wheel, visible to everyone, makes results feel more trustworthy than a software RNG. See our full breakdown in <a href="/crazy-time-is-it-rigged">Is Crazy Time Rigged?</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How Crazy Time Compares to Other Evolution Game Shows</h2>
    <p>
      Evolution produces several game show-format titles. Crazy Time occupies the high-variance, high-entertainment tier:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Dream Catcher</strong>: The simpler money wheel that preceded Crazy Time. No bonus rounds, lower max payout. Good for beginners learning the wheel format.</li>
      <li><strong>Monopoly Live</strong>: Combines a money wheel with a 3D Monopoly board bonus. Lower maximum multipliers than Crazy Time.</li>
      <li><strong>Deal or No Deal Live</strong>: Based on the TV show format. Different structure — banker offers rather than spins.</li>
      <li><strong>Crazy Time</strong>: The most complex, highest-variance, and highest-ceiling game in Evolution's lineup. Four bonus rounds, top slot multipliers, and ×20,000 max make it the peak of the game show category.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      If Crazy Time interests you, the <a href="/crazy-time-how-it-works">How Crazy Time Works</a> page explains every mechanic in detail, and the <a href="/crazy-time-strategy">strategy guide</a> covers how to approach the game with a real bankroll.
    </p>

    <StakeCTA variant="card" text="Watch Crazy Time Live on Stake — No Sign-Up Required to View →" />

    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      {[
        { q: 'What is Crazy Time game show?', a: 'Crazy Time is a live casino game show by Evolution Gaming. A real host spins a 54-segment wheel in a live studio. Players bet on outcomes. Four bonus rounds — Coin Flip, Cash Hunt, Pachinko, and Crazy Time — can deliver multiplied payouts up to ×20,000.' },
        { q: 'Who makes the Crazy Time game show?', a: 'Evolution Gaming (Evolution AB), a Swedish company listed on Nasdaq Stockholm. They are the world\'s largest live casino supplier and license Crazy Time to online casinos globally.' },
        { q: 'When was Crazy Time released?', a: 'Crazy Time was released by Evolution Gaming in 2020 and became the world\'s most played live casino game within its first year.' },
        { q: 'Is Crazy Time a game show or a slot machine?', a: 'It is a live casino game show — not a slot. Results come from a physical spinning wheel filmed live, not a software RNG. A real human host runs each round.' },
        { q: 'Can I watch Crazy Time without betting?', a: 'Yes. Most platforms allow you to observe the live Crazy Time stream without placing bets. This is a good way to learn the game before risking real money.' },
      ].map(faq => (
        <div class="bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-4">
          <p class="font-semibold text-slate-100 mb-1 m-0">{faq.q}</p>
          <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm m-0">{faq.a}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 pt-8 border-t border-slate-700 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 text-sm">
      <a href="/crazy-time-how-it-works" class="text-amber-400 hover:text-amber-300">→ How Crazy Time works</a>
      <a href="/crazy-time-rules" class="text-amber-400 hover:text-amber-300">→ Crazy Time rules</a>
      <a href="/crazy-time-strategy" class="text-amber-400 hover:text-amber-300">→ Strategy guide</a>
      <a href="/crazy-time-bonus-rounds" class="text-amber-400 hover:text-amber-300">→ All 4 bonus rounds explained</a>
      <a href="/where-to-play-crazy-time" class="text-amber-400 hover:text-amber-300">→ Where to play</a>
      <a href="/crazy-time-is-it-rigged" class="text-amber-400 hover:text-amber-300">→ Is it rigged?</a>
    </div>

    <StakeCTA variant="sticky" />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
